                <head>Items</head>
                <p xml:id="del-2024-08-start">
                    <div type="definition" resp="#CH" modified="2024-08-05T02:07:16.235+09:00" rd-id="uuid-e6a13bf7-9ea1-48d5-9140-d2d89ad69151">
                    <p>SPEECH ACT of not only mentioning but affirming a sentence, i.e. making a
                        statement which involves a truth-claim.</p>
                </div>
                    <div type="definition" resp="#CH" modified="2024-08-05T19:50:34.202+09:00" rd-id="uuid-2f466a6c-e106-4341-a2b5-cc85c0631e17">
                    <p>LITERARY GENRE of exaggerated criticism of prevalent conditions in a society
                        or group.</p>
                </div>
                    <div type="definition" resp="#chris" modified="2024-08-30T17:27:33.426+09:00" rd-id="uuid-c8de2ba1-96b2-4644-a2b3-bca47a722786">
                        <p>HISTRIONIC way of expressing something by playfully creating an appearance of claiming its opposite, typically assuming one's playfulness to be understood by the intended audience.</p>
                        <p> The use of words to express something diametrically different from their meaning, or in a histrionically mediated sense.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div type="definition" resp="#chris" modified="2024-08-30T17:30:27.81+09:00" rd-id="uuid-3b6dbde8-ceb6-48f9-bf39-6ac2e84d2349">
                    <p>IRONY involving sarcasm.</p>
                    <p> 冷笑法 Sarcastic humorous remark.</p>
                </div>
                </p>
